Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} and @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop them onto either side of a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle the @dried oregano{1%tsp} over the white potatoes.

Toss the potatoes to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the potatoes roast, trim the @courgette{1} and slice into thick 1cm rounds.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn only every couple of minutes - this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour.

Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer the courgette to a #bowl{}. Cover with a #lid{} or #foil{} to keep warm.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl, add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, @fresh pesto{50%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for amounts).

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix well to combine. Set your dressing aside for later.

When the potatoes have 5 mins left, add the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} to the baking tray (or another one if needed). Return to the oven for the remaining time until the tomato skins begin to burst.

Once the potatoes and tomatoes have roasted, add everything to the bowl of dressing.

Add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and charred courgette to the bowl, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Share your salad between your #bowls{} and crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g} to finish.

Enjoy!